      "dayId": "20230326",
      "h1title": "Zion is the first stop",
      "h3": "A beautiful sunny day to explore Zion",
      "pdate": "Sunday, March 26, 2023",
      "pdesc": "Zion doesn't allow private vehicles for visitors so we took parked by the entrance and boarded the bus.  We had already been amazed by the canyon as we drove through Springdale, Utah.  After a nice brealfast at the B&B, we had a long hike today passing up the spur trail to Angel's Landing (we didn't have a pass) and ending up following the West Rim Trail from Scouts Lookout.  Once we were back down we added on an additional few miles to hike under and around the Emerald Garden waterfalls.  WE got a chance to stop at the Castle Dome Cafe for a couple beers before heading back.",
